    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p>This policy explains how and why OneUptime uses cookies and similar technologies on our website and products.</p>
</header>

<section>
    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>OneUptime is operated by HackerBay, Inc. ("OneUptime", "we", "us"). This Cookie Policy explains what cookies are, which cookies we use, why we use them, and how you can control them. It should be read together with our <a href="/legal/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

    <h3>What are cookies?</h3>
    <p>Cookies are small text files that a website places on your device (computer, tablet, or phone) when you visit. They let the website remember your actions and preferences (such as login, language, or display settings) over a period of time, so you don't have to re-enter them each time you come back or browse between pages.</p>
    <p>We also use similar technologies such as <strong>web beacons</strong> (small transparent images used to measure email opens or page views), <strong>pixels</strong>, <strong>local storage</strong>, and <strong>session storage</strong>. In this policy, "cookies" refers to all of these technologies collectively.</p>

    <h3>First-party vs. third-party cookies</h3>
    <p><strong>First-party cookies</strong> are set by OneUptime directly when you visit our Website or use our products. <strong>Third-party cookies</strong> are set by services we embed — for example analytics, support chat, or video players. Third-party cookies are controlled by those services, and their use is governed by the respective provider's privacy policy.</p>

    <h3>Categories of cookies we use</h3>

    <h4>1. Strictly necessary cookies</h4>
    <p>These cookies are essential for the Website and our products to work. They enable core functionality such as signing you in, keeping your session secure, load balancing, remembering items in a form, and recording your cookie preferences. <strong>Strictly necessary cookies cannot be switched off</strong> — if you block them, parts of the Website will not function. They do not store any personally identifiable information for marketing purposes.</p>

    <h4>2. Functional cookies</h4>
    <p>These cookies allow us to remember choices you make (such as your language, region, or display preferences) to provide a more personalized experience. If you disable these, some parts of the Website may not work as expected.</p>

    <h4>3. Analytics / performance cookies</h4>
    <p>These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with the Website — which pages are most visited, how visitors move through the site, and whether they encounter errors. The information is aggregated and used to improve the Website. Where required by law, these cookies are only set with your consent.</p>

    <h4>4. Marketing cookies</h4>
    <p>These cookies are used to measure the effectiveness of our marketing and, where applicable, to show you relevant content on other websites. We only set marketing cookies <strong>with your consent</strong>. You can withdraw consent at any time through the cookie banner on our Website.</p>

    <h3>How long do cookies stay on your device?</h3>
    <p>Cookies fall into two time-based categories:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Session cookies</strong> — temporary cookies that are deleted when you close your browser.</li>
        <li><strong>Persistent cookies</strong> — remain on your device for a set period (usually between 30 days and 24 months) or until you delete them manually.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Do we sell your data via cookies?</h3>
    <p><strong>No.</strong> OneUptime does not sell your personal information, and we do not share it for cross-context behavioral advertising as those terms are defined under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA/CPRA).</p>

    <h3>Your choices: managing cookies</h3>
    <p>You have several ways to control cookies:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Cookie banner</strong> — when you first visit our Website, you will be shown a cookie banner where you can accept or reject non-essential cookies. You can change your preferences at any time by clicking the cookie settings link in the footer.</li>
        <li><strong>Browser settings</strong> — most browsers allow you to view, delete, and block cookies. Instructions are available for <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647">Chrome</a>, <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enhanced-tracking-protection-firefox-desktop">Firefox</a>, <a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac">Safari</a>, and <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09">Edge</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Do Not Track</strong> — we do not currently respond to browser "Do Not Track" signals, as there is no common industry standard, but we honor Global Privacy Control (GPC) signals where legally required.</li>
        <li><strong>Opting out of analytics</strong> — you can install the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a> if you wish to opt out of Google Analytics tracking.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Please note that blocking or deleting cookies may affect your experience on the Website, and some features may not work correctly.</p>

    <h3>Cookies in the OneUptime product</h3>
    <p>When you sign in to the OneUptime product, we use strictly necessary cookies to maintain your session, keep your account secure, and remember your in-product preferences. These cookies are not optional — without them, the product cannot function. We do not use marketing cookies inside the product.</p>

    <h3>Changes to this Cookie Policy</h3>
    <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in the cookies we use or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. The "last updated" date at the top of this page indicates when it was most recently revised. If we make material changes, we will provide reasonable advance notice — for example, by email to account holders or a prominent notice on the Website.</p>

    <h3>Contact us</h3>
    <p>If you have questions about our use of cookies, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@oneuptime.com">privacy@oneuptime.com</a>.</p>
</section>
